  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build 6 toilet facilities for 300 people of Swada</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite the effort to end open defecation by 2030, Swada, a village considered as the most deprived village amongst 160 villages in Ga South Municipality has no single toilet facility. This has resulted to the practice of open defecation which contributes to the contaminating effects of open defecation particularly on women and children. The project would improve access to sanitation which is a critical step towards reducing the impact of diseases and making open defecation unattractive.</narrative>
  </description>
